author: @user-cf3rs9ud6x
text: clc; clear; close x=[60 65 70 75 80 85 90 95 ];  // note the increment in x is 5. Better to have data with smaller increaments. f=[3 21 150 335 326 135 26 4]; mean_x=(sum(x.*f))/sum(f); d=(x-mean_x); f_d=f.*d f_d_square=f.*d.^2 N=sum(f) variance_x=sum(f_d_square)/N;  sigma_x=variance_x^(1/2) xnew=55:100; pdf= (1/(sigma_x*sqrt(2*%pi))) * exp(-((xnew-mean_x).^2)/(2*variance_x)); Expected_freq=N*pdf   figure(1); subplot(311) bar(x,f) xlabel('x--->'); ylabel('True Frequency'); legend(['True Frequency']); subplot(312) plot(xnew,pdf); xlabel('x--->'); ylabel('pdf'); legend(['Estimated pdf']);  subplot(313) bar(xnew,Expected_freq) xlabel('x--->'); ylabel('Expected Frequency'); legend(['Expected Frequency']); disp(mean_x, 'Mean of normal distribution =') disp(variance_x, 'Variance of normal distribution =')
